# Proving artifacts for in-browser snarkjs (FIN-027, option 2).
#
# CRITICAL: the .wasm (witness generator) and the .zkey (proving key) MUST come
# from the SAME build as the DEPLOYED verifying key — the Railway `ceremony`
# container (circom 2.1.9), NOT the local `circuits/build` (a different circom
# build whose witness layout mismatches the deployed zkey → "Invalid witness
# length" in the browser). Both were exfiltrated from Railway and verified by
# sha256 + a full fullProve→verify against the deployed VK.
#
# The .wasm are small and committed (the Railway-built ones); the .zkey are large
# (shield 31MB / unshield 64MB / transfer 110MB) and DEMO-only (single-party
# ceremony, invariant #10) — never committed. Copy the .zkey from Railway:
#   railway ssh --service ceremony "base64 -w0 setup/build/<c>/<c>.zkey" 2>/dev/null \
#     | base64 -d > public/artifacts/<c>/<c>.zkey
#
# DEPLOY (Vercel / any git deploy): the .zkey CANNOT ride the deploy — they are
# gitignored AND transfer.zkey (~105MB) exceeds GitHub's 100MB file cap. Host them
# externally (Cloudflare R2 / S3 / a GitHub Release, CORS + HTTP range enabled) and
# set NEXT_PUBLIC_ZKEY_BASE (or per-circuit NEXT_PUBLIC_ZKEY_URL_<CIRCUIT>) in the
# deploy env. The .wasm stay committed and are served from /artifacts. See lib/config.ts.
*.zkey
